Most of the food here are days old and exposed to fly's, roaches and rodents. The pastries are dry and not made on premises. You get the hot meals, cold. I have tries these places many times over the years and found the dishes appalling. It's a shame that because of the extremely high rents that these restaurants have to pay, causes these businesses to use and make sub standard food. I can tell you as a fact that the various meats are always exposed to fly's that feed on the doggy poop and then make there way to the cold-cuts for the sandwiches. SUBWAY restaurant on Jerome Ave. with the Hispanic and Chinese  restaurants all suffer the same horrible conditions. I can tell you that after living here for over 40 years, that there hasn't been not one enjoyable and decent restaurant in this community and Key Food the leader of this fowl and sub-standard food distributor has seen to it that no other super- market or quality restaurants move into this area.
